To solve the above technical problems, the technical scheme adopted by the embodiments is: An exemplary embodiment of an integrated pet harness with a pet leash, comprising: a flexible back pad and a flexible chest pad, a pair of first connecting straps and a second connecting strap, which are oppositely arranged, and further comprising:


The telescopic traction rope is connected to the flexible back pad, and the telescopic traction rope can be accommodated in the flexible back pad.

The front end of the flexible back gasket is provided with a pair of first extension portions extending to both sides respectively, and the rear end of the flexible back gasket is provided with a pair of second extension portions extending to both sides respectively;

The front end of the flexible chest pad is provided with a pair of third extensions extending to both sides respectively;

A pair of first connecting straps are respectively fixed to the front ends of the flexible back pads, and two ends of the pair of first connecting straps are respectively protruded from the pair of first extending portions and are respectively connected to the pair of third extending portions;

The second connecting strip passes through the rear end of the flexible back pad, and two ends of the second connecting strip are respectively connected to a pair of second extending portions correspondingly.

Further, it also includes: 


a first fastener, comprising a hollow first fastener frame, a first crossbar arranged on the first fastener frame, and the first crossbar divides the hollow part of the first fastener frame into a pair of first through-holes;

One end of the first connecting belt is inserted between a pair of first through-holes from one side of the first crossbar, the first fastener is passed through the first connecting belt, and the first connecting belt is on the flexible back pad. A first movable segment with a movable adjustable length is formed between the sheet and the first fastener;

After one end of the first connecting belt is passed out of the first fastener, it is again inserted between a pair of first through-holes from one side of the first crossbar, and is fixedly connected after being passed out of the first fastener again. A first collar is formed on the first connecting belt and one end of the first connecting belt is sleeved on the first crossbar, and finally, the first connecting belt is fixedly connected to the third extension part, and the first connecting belt is on the third extension part. The length between the first fastener and the connection between the first connection band and the third extension part can be adjusted movably corresponding to the length of the first movable segment.

Further, it also includes: 


The second fastener includes a hollow second fastener frame, and a second crossbar disposed on the second fastener frame, and the second crossbar divides the hollow portion of the second fastener frame into a pair of second through holes;

The third fastener includes a hollow third fastener frame, and a third crossbar arranged on the third fastener frame. The third crossbar divides the hollow part of the third fastener frame into a pair of third through-holes, which are provided with The buckle structure on the third buckle frame; One end of the second connecting strip is inserted from one side of the second crossbar between a pair of second through-holes, and the second fastener is passed through the second connecting strip, and the second connecting strip is on the second buckle. A second movable segment with adjustable length is formed between the piece and the flexible chest pad;

After one end of the second connecting belt is passed through the second fastener, one end of the second connecting belt is inserted between a pair of third through-holes from one side of the third crossbar, and the third fastener is passed through the pair of third through holes. set on the second connecting belt;

After one end of the second connecting belt is passed out of the third fastener, it is inserted between a pair of second through-holes from one side of the second transverse rod and finally passes out of the second fastener.

